Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop
them on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss
to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}, discard the core and seeds then chop into 2cm chunks.
Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the
@British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}, breaking it up with a
#spoon{} as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Add the pepper to the beef, stir together,
and cook until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir the @Mexican style spice mix{1} and garlic into the beef and cook for ~{1%minute}.
Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and @water{50%ml}. Stir in the
@beef stock paste{10%g}, bring to the boil then reduce the heat to medium. Allow to simmer
and thicken, stirring occasionally until there is almost no liquid left, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if the mixture looks a little dry.

Meanwhile, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone, turn the
avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then
scoop out the insides into a #bowl{}. Halve the @lime{1/2} and add a squeeze of juice and
a pinch of salt and pepper. Mash with a #fork{}. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime
juice if required. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the sauce has thickened, season with salt and pepper to taste. Spoon into an
#ovenproof dish{}. Top with the roasted potato and sprinkle over the cheese. Place on the
top shelf of your oven and bake until the cheese has melted and is nice and golden,
~{10-12%minutes}. Once golden, serve in deep #bowls{} with a dollop of guacamole. Enjoy!